To create an AWS user with full EC2 access restricted to a specific region using the AWS CLI, you first need to create the user and then create a policy that limits their access. Finally, you attach this policy to the user. 
1. Create the IAM User:
Code

aws iam create-user --user-name my-ec2-user
2. Create the IAM Policy:
This policy limits access to EC2 to the specified region. Replace us-east-1 with your desired region. 
Code

{
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Statement": [
        {
            "Effect": "Allow",
            "Action": [
                "ec2:*"
            ],
            "Resource": "*",
            "Condition": {
                "StringEquals": {
                    "ec2:Region": "us-east-1"
                }
            }
        }
    ]
}
Save this JSON to a file (e.g., ec2-region-policy.json). 
3. Create the Policy using the CLI: 
Code

aws iam create-policy --policy-name ec2-region-policy --policy-document file://ec2-region-policy.json
4. Attach the Policy to the User:
Code

aws iam attach-user-policy --user-name my-ec2-user --policy-arn arn:aws:iam::YOUR-ACCOUNT-ID:policy/ec2-region-policy
Replace YOUR-ACCOUNT-ID with your actual AWS account ID
